Video Game Creation Syllabus 
(this syllabus is a working document and changes can be requested on GitHub as students may have ideas on how to make this class more relevant and better!)

Explore video game development, including game design, gameplay development, and asset creation. 
Students will submit their game they developed in a video game competition in the fall.

Week 1: Explore Games That Work - Genres, Strategies, Storylines, Rules
Week 2: Game Components - Characters, Tokens, Scores, Objectives
Week 3: Platforms - Explore Scratch, Godot, Unity
Week 4: Project Setup & Game Loop - setting up development environments, understanding how games update and render continuously
Week 5: Input & Controls - implementing player controls, responsive input handling, basic movement mechanics
Week 6:  Collision Detection & Physics - basic physics, collision responses, object interactions
Week 7: Scoring and State Management - tracking game state, score systems, win/lose conditions
Week 8: Enemies & AI - creating non-player characters, simple enemy behavior patterns, pathfinding basics
Week 9: Levels & Progressions - designing level structure, difficulty curves, level transitions
Week 10: Environments & Tilemaps - worldbuilding, tilemap editors, parallax scrolling
Week 11: Audio & Sound Effects - adding background music, sound effects, audio management
Week 12: Visual Effects & Animations - particle effects, sprite animations, screen shake, polish techniques
Week 13: UI/Menus - creating start menus, pause screens, settings HUD design
Week 14: Data Persistence - saving/loading game progress, managing player data, high scores
Week 15: Game Development Sprint 1 - put together in a game, peer code review
Week 16: Game Development Sprint 2 - continued development, playtesting, bug fixes, feedback iteration
Week 17: Playtesting & Iteration - formal playtesting sessions, gather user feedback, implement improvements
Week 18: Submission Preparation & Showcase - final polish, documentation, game submission, project retrospective
